Mostly pickup groups don't want a wizard because they don't know what I can add.  They will take a paladin's pathetic heal over my huge damage, because they don't realize how quickly I can burn something down.  Now, this is a LOT to do with education of the less intelligent masses.  I have made many friends by showing them how successfull a wiz-mag-bard-pal-rog-ran group can be.  I also know how to direct such a group cause I've done so many of them.  I actually prefer those &quot;odd&quot; combinations.  But many people don't, and I think increasing what we can offer to a group will help show the uninformed masses how worthwhile we are.<br>
I don't think we need a general damage increase - maybe just one that affects us in groups.  I LOVE being a wizard, and wouldn't have it any other way.  I can't wait for higher levels, and higher damage.  I dream of having enough mana to kill myself 10 times over, rather than just 4. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
But that's just me. <p><br>Aniar Orrenson
