<br>
&quot;What do you think of those familiars?&quot;<br>
&quot;Great, lets give them 4 of those.&quot;<br>
&quot;Sweet, well that half of the spells we had to come up with. Good job.&quot;<br>
<br>
I look at the other spell lines and I see the depth to them. New buffs, new DD's, new AE's etc. I see that every aspect was thought about and modified. I just have this nagging feeling that not as much thought is put into our spells. A small dmg shield is useful to a wizard in a narrow range. The roaming eye is only good in very specific situations. The new DD and root is good for a few levels. <br>
<br>
These just seem like little pokes and prods to our class, nothing much of note. Do remember that I am still hoping against hope that the familiars prove me wrong on all of this.<br>
